news.title: Ludhiana: Engineers' body approaches CMO against illegal colonies under Glada
news.para: Members of Council of Engineers (COE) alleged that despite officials claiming otherwise, there has been little check on illegal colonies.

news.title: Indore: Illegally developed 20 acres may now be home for poor
news.para: Instructions have been issued to IMC, T&CP and the revenue department to put a ban on giving any permission along with registration of property (sale/purchase) of the land. Market value of said around 20 acres of land is stated to be around Rs 500 Crore.

news.title: Panchkula civic body to build houses to rehabilitate slum dwellers
news.para: The houses would be constructed under the Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojna. The agenda point will be brought in for approval in the forthcoming MC house meet slated for September 29, along with 24 other points.

news.title: Pune civic body seals 1,355 properties over tax dues
news.para: The civic administration has recovered Rs92 crore from some owners who cleared the dues after the sealing process started.

news.title: No houses built in three districts of Rajasthan under PMAY-Gramin
news.para: The nine districts are Sikar, Dholpur, Jaipur, Bundi, Pali, Churu, Nagaur, Dungarpur and Baran. It also revealed that out of 59,402 houses under construction (sanctioned between 2016-17 to 2020-21), only 1857 were completed in the last 15 days.

news.title: Pune civic body to team up with MSEDCL, fix property misuse
news.para: Once misuse is detected, action includes charging commercial tax to property owners. A special recovery drive will be undertaken for charging dues, the levy imposed at commercial rates.

news.title: Bombay HC sets aside reservations on Cidco plots
news.para: ​Cidco had alleged that NMMC had illegally exercised its power. The reservations form part of the draft development plan. Builders have moved HC and filed two separate PILs.

news.title: Hike in house tax to be raised in Kanpur civic body meet to begin on Sep 24
news.para: According to corporators, the KMC had appointed a company to conduct a survey of the houses of the city through a geographic information system

news.title: Noida: Developers need 3-5 years to pay for plots post-allotment, says Credai
news.para: According to Credai members, both are two extremes and a middle path - like a three to five-year window - should be chosen as this new rule would allow only developers with big pockets to remain in the business.

news.title: Maharashtra: SC clarifies eco-sensitive zone curbs, relief for developers
news.para: In a relief to developers and flat-buyers, the Supreme Court has upheld the eco-sensitive zone (ESZ) notifications for the Sanjay Gandhi National Park (SGNP) in 2016 and for the Thane Creek Flamingo Sanctuary in 2021.

news.title: Bureau of Immigration issues lookout circular against Odyssa Homes' director
news.para: The accused Manoj Kumar Panda is the director of Odyssa Homes and Commercials Private Limited. He has been absconding since a criminal case was filed against him, police said Friday.

news.title: Blackstone to sell $400 million stake in Embassy REIT: Sources
news.para: Abu Dhabi's sovereign wealth fund, one of the world's largest, is likely to pick up at least half of the stake that Blackstone is to sell, one of the sources said.

news.title: Over 11,000 flats' possession to be given to Amrapali buyers in 2-3 months
news.para: ​A bench of Chief Justice UU Lalit and Justice Bela M Trivedi was informed by court receiver senior advocate R Venkataramani that in the upcoming festive season next month 5,428 flats which have been completed by the NBCC will be given to the home buyers with electricity and water connection.

news.title: Ulhasnagar: Building declared 'dangerous', yet five flats were occupied
news.para: Over the past 12 years, 38 buildings in Ulhasnagar have collapsed, some partially, killing 42 people and leaving at least 5,000 homeless.

news.title: UP RERA imposes penalty against 13 developers
news.para: The authority is making constant efforts to ensure enforcement of its orders and provide speedy justice to the aggrieved allottees. The action of penalty against the guilty promoters is an important step towards compelling them to comply with the orders of the authority.
